# Amber Component 2 — Bright Data credentials TEMPLATE (committed; NO real secrets).
# Copy to code/.env (gitignored) and fill in real values, OR export these in your
# shell. amber/capture/credentials.py reads the process env first, then code/.env.
#
# Two modes are supported; provide EITHER the proxy set OR the API token.
#
# --- proxy mode (PREFERRED — sticky sessions give the within-country control) ---
# Your customer id, the residential zone name, and that zone's password.
BRIGHTDATA_CUSTOMER_ID=hl_xxxxxxxx
BRIGHTDATA_ZONE=residential_zone_name
BRIGHTDATA_ZONE_PASSWORD=your_zone_password
#
# --- api mode (Web Unlocker / request API) ---
# A single API token (used if the proxy set above is not fully present).
# BRIGHTDATA_API_TOKEN=your_api_token
